<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-028-265 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 470 939</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 28 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Comdex: Windows products big winner for 1991. (Microsoft Windows3.0 graphical user interface)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mallory, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Products).andO;Product:   Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (evaluation)Microsoft Excel for Windows 3.0 (Spreadsheet software)(evaluation)Visual Basic (Program development software) (evaluation)Microsoft Word for Windows 2.0 (Word processing software)(evaluation).andO;Topic:     Achievements and AwardsComputer industryComdex-FallTrade showsGraphical user interfaceSoftware packagesSpreadsheetsProgram development softwareWord processing software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Comdex: Windows Products Big Winner for 1991 10/28/91 LAS VEGAS, NEVADA,U.S.A., 1991 OCT 28 (NB) -- Microsoft Windows applications were a big hitthis year, winning many of the major awards at this year's fall COMDEX in LasVegas, as well as a number of other major awards.andM;Excel for Windows version 3.0 walked off with the Most Valuable Product awardfrom PC Computing magazine, as well as the Product of the Year award in theapplications software category from Systems Integration Magazine.andP;  Bothawards were in the spreadsheet category.andP;  Excel for Windows was also judgedthe number one spreadsheet by PC Week, Software Digest, and the NationalSoftware Testing Laboratory, and was cited as the highest rated product byInfoWorld.andM;In the development tools category, Microsoft Visual Basic version 1.0 forWindows won the PC Magazine Technical Excellence Award and the Most ValuableProduct Award from PC Computing.andP;  Visual Basic had already picked up Best ofShow and Best of Spring COMDEX from Byte in the windows development toolscategory at spring's COMDEX in Atlanta.andM;Byte magazine's Best of Fall COMDEX in the application category went to Wordfor Windows version 2.0, which was unveiled during the show.andP;  In addition,Word for Windows collected Byte's Award of Distinction, InfoWorld's Productof the Year award, and PC Magazine's Best of 1990 designation.andM;Project for Windows walked away with the Best of 1990 award from InfoWorld,Best Buy award from PC World, Best Project Manager for Windows from PC Week,Editor's Choice from PC Magazine, Readers' Choice from Byte, and was chosenas the number one product by Software Digest.andM;Microsoft Powerpoint for Windows was selected for PC Magazine's Best of 1990award and also got the magazine's Editor's Choice award, in addition to PCWeek's Analysts' Choice award, and was picked by PC World as the best buy.andM;Microsoft Works for Windows got the Gold Award in the integrated softwarecategory at the Windows Forum earlier this year.andM;(Jim Mallory/19911026/Press contact: Karen Meredith, Microsoft, 206-882-8080)</TEXT></DOC>